WEBVTT

00:06.172 --> 00:09.134
(police siren whooping)

00:09.217 --> 00:10.885
(brakes creak)

00:10.969 --> 00:14.097
(police radio chatter)

00:21.062 --> 00:23.606
-What did he do?
-Dealing fentanyl.

00:23.690 --> 00:25.275
Really?

00:26.443 --> 00:27.777
Hey, what's up, Sam?

00:27.861 --> 00:29.821
-Hey, Drew.
-(car door shuts)

00:29.904 --> 00:33.241
(whimsical theme playing)

00:33.324 --> 00:34.826
(screen door opens)

00:34.909 --> 00:38.037
(keys rattle)

00:38.121 --> 00:39.497
(door shuts)

00:42.041 --> 00:43.334
Hey.

00:43.418 --> 00:46.504
-Hi. Good morning. Drive.
-Good morning.

00:46.588 --> 00:49.299
Sam:
I am amped the fuck up!

00:50.842 --> 00:53.470
I have been racking my brain,
trying to figure out

00:53.553 --> 00:56.014
why the fuck was Rick
at choir practice?

00:56.097 --> 00:58.183
Anyone can go to
choir practice.

00:58.266 --> 01:00.143
Ah, that dumb fuck.
No fucking way

01:00.226 --> 01:03.396
he'd show up there on his own.
No fuckin' way!

01:03.480 --> 01:06.232
You know, I was over Tricia's
house, and he's laying around,

01:06.316 --> 01:08.485
playing games like
he always fucking does,

01:08.568 --> 01:10.862
and I see something sticking
out of his pants, and I'm like

01:10.945 --> 01:12.155
-what the fuck is that?
-(laughs)

01:12.238 --> 01:16.117
And it was a big old
fuckin' wad of fuckin' cash!

01:16.201 --> 01:18.912
Well, sounds like
business is good. Great.

01:18.995 --> 01:21.372
That motherfucker doesn't have
two nickels to rub together.

01:21.456 --> 01:24.459
His allowance is like,
I don't know, 30 bucks
a week or something.

01:24.542 --> 01:26.920
-Oh. That is small.
-Yeah,

01:27.003 --> 01:28.797
so how the fuck does
he have all that money

01:28.880 --> 01:32.342
in his fuckin' pants,
and what the fuck
is it fuckin' for?

01:32.425 --> 01:33.885
Huh?

01:33.968 --> 01:36.679
Think about it.
Think about it.

01:37.806 --> 01:39.182
-Okay.
-Drugs.

01:39.265 --> 01:41.017
-Oh. (laughs)
-Yeah.

01:41.100 --> 01:42.811
-Really?
-It's everywhere, man.

01:42.894 --> 01:44.813
Oh my god, pull in here.

01:44.896 --> 01:47.232
Joel:
Oh, Randy's working!

01:48.233 --> 01:49.943
-Randy: Hey, Joel.
-Hey.

01:50.026 --> 01:52.153
Oh. Hey, Sam.
I didn't see you there.
Uh, hang on a sec.

01:52.237 --> 01:53.822
Oh no, that's okay.
If I have any more coffee,

01:53.905 --> 01:55.824
-my heart's gonna explode.
Now, Joel--
-(laughs)

01:55.907 --> 01:57.826
So, uh, when'd you
two start hanging out.

01:57.909 --> 01:59.536
Oh. Well, um, okay,

01:59.619 --> 02:02.121
-you know I work at--
-It's not the time, Joel.
Joel, Joel, Joel.

02:02.205 --> 02:03.248
Sorry, Randy.
We have to go.

02:03.331 --> 02:04.999
-Okay. No problem.
-Sam: Thank you. Okay.

02:05.083 --> 02:08.294
-Pull over there
by the dumpster.
-Say hi to Tammy. (laughs)

02:10.922 --> 02:12.549
(shifts into park)

02:12.632 --> 02:14.759
Oh my god!
Are we buying drugs?

02:14.843 --> 02:16.553
No!

02:16.636 --> 02:18.346
Well, it's just that you
had me park by a dumpster,

02:18.429 --> 02:19.764
and you're talking
about all this stuff--

02:19.848 --> 02:23.143
Joel, Rick is selling drugs.

02:23.226 --> 02:25.895
What? No. Rick-Rick?
Are you sure?

02:25.979 --> 02:27.730
Well, if he is,
I'm gonna cut his dick off.

02:27.814 --> 02:30.692
That's Shannon's dad!
Fuck.

02:30.775 --> 02:32.193
Look, he stops
here every morning.

02:32.277 --> 02:33.778
He's a very
predictable dude.

02:33.862 --> 02:35.155
At least,
I thought he was.

02:35.238 --> 02:37.198
You know,
I've stalked people online,

02:37.282 --> 02:38.700
but I haven't stalked
anybody in person in,

02:38.783 --> 02:39.868
like, since high school,

02:39.951 --> 02:42.078
so this is kinda
exciting for me. (laughs)

02:42.161 --> 02:44.414
-Sam: Oh, that's him! Get down!
-Joel: Oh god.

02:44.497 --> 02:46.374
-Joel: Huh!
-Sam: Ew, that's your bottom!

02:46.457 --> 02:48.376
Joel: (laughs)
This is so intense!

02:48.459 --> 02:49.961
Don't sniff!

02:51.212 --> 02:54.340
(whimsical music)

03:01.347 --> 03:02.682
(inaudible sigh)

03:07.854 --> 03:09.939
Woman: (laughs)
It looks like Toto!

03:14.986 --> 03:17.196
Couldn't it be like a gambling
problem or something?

03:17.280 --> 03:20.700
No. Rick is way too unlucky.
To his credit, he knows it.

03:20.783 --> 03:22.160
Oh my god,
embezzling.

03:22.243 --> 03:24.245
Joel, I've given this
a lot of thought.

03:24.329 --> 03:25.496
It has to be drugs.

03:25.580 --> 03:27.290
Why else would Rick
be at choir practice

03:27.373 --> 03:29.584
-if it wasn't to move
some fucking product?
-I really don't think

03:29.667 --> 03:32.170
anyone there would be
buying... Oh my god.

03:32.253 --> 03:33.296
-What?
-Oh shit, shit, shit.

03:33.379 --> 03:34.505
He's stopping.
He's pulling over!

03:34.589 --> 03:36.507
-He's pulling over!
-He can't see me!

03:36.591 --> 03:37.967
-Okay. Okay.
-Okay, just be cool.

03:38.051 --> 03:40.678
Pull a casual U-turn and park
where you can have eyes on him.

03:40.762 --> 03:41.763
What's a casual U-turn?

03:41.846 --> 03:43.306
I can't be casual
about breaking the law.

03:43.389 --> 03:46.017
-Joel, just turn
around and park!
-Okay, okay!

03:47.060 --> 03:49.520
Joel, park over there!

03:49.604 --> 03:52.482
-Oh, I don't like that spot--
-Joel, park the fucking car!

03:52.565 --> 03:54.067
I like to have shade!

03:54.150 --> 03:55.902
Sam:
Oh my god, Joel!

03:55.985 --> 03:57.779
Oh, Jesus Christ.

03:57.862 --> 03:59.113
All clear.

03:59.197 --> 04:00.907
-(Joel sighs)
-(chair thuds)

04:00.990 --> 04:04.410
Sam:
Oh my god. This is some
shady fuckin' shit.

04:04.494 --> 04:05.578
(mechanical whirring)

04:05.662 --> 04:07.705
-Oh my god.
-What?

04:07.789 --> 04:09.749
-What?
-It's Bill Baker.

04:09.832 --> 04:11.459
Sam:
Who's Bill Baker?

04:11.542 --> 04:14.212
Joel:
Bill Baker, the chainsaw artist.
He's a genius.

04:14.295 --> 04:17.006
His beaver is
installed in Town Hall.

04:17.090 --> 04:19.425
-That's pretty cool.
-What's he making?

04:19.509 --> 04:21.719
-(chainsaw whirring)
-Excuse me.

04:25.223 --> 04:27.183
-I'm a birder. (laughs)
-What are the chances?

04:27.266 --> 04:30.311
-(whirring)
-Wait, gimme those.

04:30.395 --> 04:33.690
-But I'm-- I'm using
them right now, but...
-Just give them.

04:36.901 --> 04:38.903
-Joel: What is it?
-Sam: Okay. Okay, no, no, no.

04:38.987 --> 04:40.863
-Get out your phone.
-Joel: Oh.

04:40.947 --> 04:42.198
And get ready to hit record

04:42.281 --> 04:44.659
as soon as shit
starts going down.

04:45.410 --> 04:46.911
Copy that.

04:48.621 --> 04:51.624
Sam:
You gonna get a little hot dog?
You sick fuck. Oh yeah.

04:51.708 --> 04:55.044
-How am I gonna know when
shit is starting to go down.
-Oh, you're gonna know.

04:55.128 --> 04:57.588
(chainsaw whirring)

04:57.672 --> 05:00.091
-(sighs)
-But how?

05:00.174 --> 05:02.468
Tricia:
I just saw Poppy's
new window display.

05:02.552 --> 05:04.721
They have a Toto
in a little raincoat.

05:04.804 --> 05:07.015
I know. I saw it.
I freaked out.

05:07.098 --> 05:08.766
-It's disarmingly adorable.
-Well,

05:08.850 --> 05:10.393
we are gonna fight

05:10.476 --> 05:12.562
fire with fire.

05:12.645 --> 05:15.732
(whirring)

05:19.110 --> 05:22.238
He hasn't moved for
40 fuckin' minutes.

05:22.322 --> 05:25.366
Maybe he just
loves chainsaw art.

05:25.450 --> 05:28.745
-Joel...
-I mean, who doesn't?

05:28.828 --> 05:32.248
Man, I'm really starting to
crash from all that caffeine.

05:32.331 --> 05:34.500
I could use, like,
a little snack or...

05:34.584 --> 05:36.085
(chainsaw continues)

05:36.169 --> 05:38.755
I might have something
in the winter survival kit.

05:38.838 --> 05:40.923
-Oh.
-Like an old granola bar.

05:41.007 --> 05:44.052
-Mm, I love
an old granola bar.
-(laughs)

05:44.135 --> 05:45.386
Hit me.

05:45.470 --> 05:48.890
One time, I drove off the road
during this crazy blizzard.

05:48.973 --> 05:50.308
You don't even wanna know

05:50.391 --> 05:53.352
-the things I had to do
to get through.
-Um, yes, I do!

05:54.062 --> 05:55.188
(laughs)

05:55.271 --> 05:57.940
-No.
-Come on, just tell me
one little thing.

05:59.233 --> 06:01.527
-No.
-What, did you, um...

06:02.653 --> 06:05.281
take yourself a little cup...

06:05.364 --> 06:07.742
take your little, or big...

06:07.825 --> 06:09.786
-(laughs)
-...penis out,

06:09.869 --> 06:11.579
fill up that cup

06:11.662 --> 06:13.289
