for dinner.
Is that so wrong?

12:49.268 --> 12:52.062
No, that is so right,
Pastor Deb.

12:52.146 --> 12:53.981
Emmet? Margs?

12:54.064 --> 12:56.275
-Okay.
-Joel: Okay, great.

12:56.358 --> 12:58.319
You two go on ahead.
I'm gonna stay behind though

12:58.402 --> 13:00.404
because I wanna work on
some new choir music.

13:00.488 --> 13:03.240
Oh. Right.

13:03.324 --> 13:05.075
I can't wait
to hear it.

13:06.744 --> 13:08.996
Yeah, it's a really
great essay, Shan.
I love it.

13:09.079 --> 13:12.291
And that stuff about you and
Grandpa with the popcorn garden?

13:12.374 --> 13:15.002
-(laughs)
-Hit me right in
the heart. So sweet.

13:15.085 --> 13:17.254
I didn't know that you asked
Sam to help with your essay.

13:17.338 --> 13:19.048
Oh, yeah. I mean,
it's her job.

13:19.131 --> 13:19.965
Yeah, I know it's her job,

13:20.049 --> 13:22.927
but I was accepted
everywhere

13:23.010 --> 13:25.012
I applied to, so...

13:25.095 --> 13:26.514
You know, why don't
you ask your mom

13:26.597 --> 13:27.973
to help you with that
community service part

13:28.057 --> 13:29.892
-you've been struggling with.
-I'd be happy to! Scooch.

13:29.975 --> 13:31.936
It'll be great.
(sighs)

13:32.019 --> 13:34.271
And I am gonna
go check on Mom

13:34.355 --> 13:37.107
